          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "Draw random samples from a normal (Gaussian) distribution."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Summary"
    },
    {
      "blocks": [
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "The probability density function of the normal distribution, first\nderived by De Moivre and 200 years later by both Gauss and Laplace\nindependently "
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "[2]_"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": ", is often called the bell curve because of\nits characteristic shape (see the example below)."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "The normal distributions occurs often in nature.  For example, it\ndescribes the commonly occurring distribution of samples influenced\nby a large number of tiny, random disturbances, each with its own\nunique distribution "
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "[2]_"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "argument_inline": [],
          "content_blocks": [
            {
              "inline": [
                {
                  "kind": "text",
                  "text": "New code should use the "
                },
                {
                  "external_url": "https://numpy.org/doc/stable/reference/generated/numpy.random.Generator.normal.html",
                  "href": "",
                  "kind": "link",
                  "target": "random.Generator.normal",
                  "text": "normal"
                },
                {
                  "kind": "text",
                  "text": "\nmethod of a "
                },
                {
                  "external_url": "https://numpy.org/doc/stable/reference/generated/numpy.random.Generator.html",
                  "href": "",
                  "kind": "link",
                  "target": "random.Generator",
                  "text": "Generator"
                },
                {
                  "kind": "text",
                  "text": " instance instead;\nplease see the "
                },
                {
                  "display_text": "random-quick-start",
                  "explicit_title": false,
                  "external_url": "https://numpy.org/doc/stable/reference/generated/numpy.random-quick-start.html",
                  "href": "",
                  "kind": "role_reference",
