    {
      "blocks": [
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "The probability density for the Gaussian distribution is"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "formulas": [
            "p(x) = \\frac{1}{\\sqrt{ 2 \\pi \\sigma^2 }} e^{ - \\frac{ (x - \\mu)^2 } {2 \\sigma^2} },"
          ],
          "type": "math_block"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "where "
            },
            {
              "kind": "math",
              "latex": "\\mu"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " is the mean and "
            },
            {
              "kind": "math",
              "latex": "\\sigma"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " the standard\ndeviation. The square of the standard deviation, "
            },
            {
              "kind": "math",
              "latex": "\\sigma^2"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": ",\nis called the variance."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "The function has its peak at the mean, and its \"spread\" increases with\nthe standard deviation (the function reaches 0.607 times its maximum at\n"
            },
            {
              "kind": "math",
              "latex": "x + \\sigma"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " and "
            },
            {
              "kind": "math",
              "latex": "x - \\sigma"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " "
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "[2]_"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": ").  This implies that\nnormal is more likely to return samples lying close to the mean, rather\nthan those far away."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Notes"
    },
    {
      "blocks": [
        {
          "raw_kind": "footnote",
          "raw_text": "1\n\nWikipedia, \"Normal distribution\",\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Normal_distribution",
          "type": "raw_block"
        },
        {
          "raw_kind": "footnote",
          "raw_text": "2\n\nP. R. Peebles Jr., \"Central Limit Theorem\" in \"Probability,\nRandom Variables and Random Signal Principles\", 4th ed., 2001,\npp. 51, 51, 125.",
          "type": "raw_block"
        }
      ],
      "title": "References"
    },
    {
      "blocks": [
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "Draw samples from the distribution:"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "lines": [
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "mu, sigma = 0, 0.1 # mean and standard deviation"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "s = we.random.normal(mu, sigma, 1000)"
            }
          ],
          "type": "doctest_block"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "Verify the mean and the standard deviation:"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "lines": [
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "abs(mu - we.mean(s))"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "0.0  # may vary"
            }
          ],
          "type": "doctest_block"
        },
        {
          "lines": [
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "abs(sigma - we.std(s, ddof=1))"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "0.1  # may vary"
            }
          ],
          "type": "doctest_block"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "Display the histogram of the samples, along with\nthe probability density function:"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "lines": [
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "count, bins, ignored = plt.hist(s, 30, density=True)"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "plt.plot(bins, 1/(sigma * we.sqrt(2 * we.pi)) *"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": "...",
              "text": "we.exp( - (bins - mu)**2 / (2 * sigma**2) ),"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": "...",
              "text": "linewidth=2, color='r')"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "plt.show()"
            }
          ],
          "type": "doctest_block"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "Two-by-four array of samples from the normal distribution with\nmean 3 and standard deviation 2.5:"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "lines": [
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "we.random.normal(3, 2.5, size=(2, 4))"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "array([[-4.49401501,  4.00950034, -1.81814867,  7.29718677],   # random"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "       [ 0.39924804,  4.68456316,  4.99394529,  4.84057254]])  # random"
            }
          ],
          "type": "doctest_block"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Examples"
    }
